%% Diagram: Background Fetch handoff from page to service worker
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant P as Page
    participant SW as Service Worker
    participant BF as Browser BackgroundFetch
    participant S as Server / Storage

    P->>SW: navigator.serviceWorker.ready
    P->>BF: reg.backgroundFetch.fetch(id,\n[Request, ...], {uploadTotal, title, icons})
    BF-->>P: BackgroundFetchRegistration

    Note over P,BF: User may navigate away or close tab

    BF->>S: HTTP request(s)
    S-->>BF: bytes / 2xx
    Note over BF: Browser pauses + resumes\nacross network changes\nshows OS-level UI

    BF->>SW: dispatch backgroundfetchsuccess
    SW->>SW: read MatchAll records,\npersist offsets / final URLs,\nshow notification

    Note over BF,SW: On failure: backgroundfetchfail\nOn user cancel: backgroundfetchabort
